name: cred-rea-fish-team-stationary-point-count-surveys-at-tau-2004
notes: Stationary Point Counts at 4 stations at each survey site were surveyed as part of Rapid Ecological Assessments conducted at 9 sites at Ta'u, Island in American Samoa in February, 2004 from the NOAA vessel Oscar Elton Sette (OES04-02). Raw survey data included species level abundance estimates.
